NNAAMMEE
       rruunn - Run a node script

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       slc run <script-file> [script-options]
       slc run

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --hh, ----hheellpp
              print usage information

       ssccrriipptt--ffiillee
              node script file to run

       Use .. to run the application in the current directory.

       If no module is specified, then slc will start REPL and load the module
       in the current directory.

